.TH "BLUETOOTHCTL-HCI" "1" "December 2024" "BlueZ" "Linux System Administration"
.SH NAME
bluetoothctl-hci \- HCI Submenu
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
\fBbluetoothctl\fP [\-\-options] [hci.commands]
.sp
\fBNOTE:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
This submenu communicates directly with the Bluetooth controller via HCI
socket, bypassing the BlueZ D\-Bus API. Commands use the Host Controller
Interface (HCI) protocol.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH COMMANDS
.SS open
.sp
Open HCI channel.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> open <index> <chan=raw,user>\fP
.TP
.B index
HCI controller index number (e.g., 0, 1, 2)
.TP
.B chan
Channel type (raw or user)
.TP
.B Example Open user channel (controller needs to be powered off first)
.nf
\fB> power off\fP
\fB> hci.open 0 user\fP
\fBHCI index 0 user channel opened\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Open user channel for HCI controller 0
.nf
\fB> hci.open 0 user\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Open user channel for HCI controller 1
.nf
\fB> hci.open 1 user\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Open user channel for HCI controller 2
.nf
\fB> hci.open 2 user\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Open raw channel for HCI controller 0
.nf
\fB> hci.open 0 raw\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Open raw channel for HCI controller 1
.nf
\fB> hci.open 1 raw\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS cmd
.sp
Send HCI command.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> cmd <opcode> [parameters...]\fP
.TP
.B opcode
HCI command opcode in hexadecimal format (e.g., 0x0c03)
.TP
.B parameters
Optional command parameters as hexadecimal bytes
.TP
.B Example Send HCI Reset command
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x0c03\fP
\fBHCI Command complete:\fP
\fB00\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send HCI Reset command (no parameters)
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x0c03\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send HCI Read Local Version Information
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x1003\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send HCI Read BD Address
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x1009\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send HCI Set Event Filter with parameter 0x01
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x0c01 0x01\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send LE Set Advertising Parameters with 2 parameters
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x200f 0x00 0x08\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send LE Set Advertising Data with length and data bytes
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x2008 0x20 0x01 0x02 0x03 0x04 0x05 0x06 0x07 0x08\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send HCI Set Event Mask command
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x0c05 0x02\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send HCI Write Scan Enable
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x0c2a 0x01\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send HCI Write Class of Device
.nf
\fB> hci.cmd 0x0c23 0x00 0x08\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS send
.sp
Send HCI data packet.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> send <type=acl,sco,iso> <handle> [data...]\fP
.TP
.B type
Packet type (acl, sco, or iso)
.TP
.B handle
Connection handle in hexadecimal format (e.g., 0x0000)
.TP
.B data
Optional data bytes in hexadecimal format
.TP
.B Example Send ACL data packet to connection handle 0x0000
.nf
\fB> hci.send acl 0x0000\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send empty ACL packet to handle 0x0000
.nf
\fB> hci.send acl 0x0000\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send ACL packet with \(dqHello\(dq data to handle 0x0001
.nf
\fB> hci.send acl 0x0001 0x48 0x65 0x6c 0x6c 0x6f\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send ACL packet with custom data to handle 0x0010
.nf
\fB> hci.send acl 0x0010 0x01 0x02 0x03 0x04\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send empty SCO packet to handle 0x0000
.nf
\fB> hci.send sco 0x0000\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send SCO packet with audio data
.nf
\fB> hci.send sco 0x0001 0xaa 0xbb 0xcc\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send SCO packet with sine wave pattern
.nf
\fB> hci.send sco 0x0002 0x80 0x00 0x80 0x00\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send empty ISO packet to handle 0x0000
.nf
\fB> hci.send iso 0x0000\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send ISO packet with sample data
.nf
\fB> hci.send iso 0x0001 0x12 0x34 0x56 0x78\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Send ISO packet for LE Audio stream
.nf
\fB> hci.send iso 0x0020 0xa0 0xa1 0xa2 0xa3\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS register
.sp
Register HCI event handler.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> register <event>\fP
.TP
.B event
HCI event code in hexadecimal format (e.g., 0x0e)
.TP
.B Example Register handler for Command Complete event
.nf
\fB> register 0x0e\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Register handler for Command Status event
.nf
\fB> register 0x0f\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Register handler for Connection Complete event
.nf
\fB> register 0x03\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Register handler for Disconnection Complete event
.nf
\fB> register 0x05\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Register handler for LE Meta events
.nf
\fB> register 0x3e\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Register handler for Inquiry Complete event
.nf
\fB> register 0x02\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Register handler for Role Change event
.nf
\fB> register 0x22\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS unregister
.sp
Unregister HCI event handler.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> unregister <event>\fP
.TP
.B event
HCI event code in hexadecimal format (e.g., 0x0e)
.TP
.B Example Unregister Command Complete event handler
.nf
\fB> unregister 0x0e\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Unregister Command Status event handler
.nf
\fB> unregister 0x0f\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Unregister Connection Complete event handler
.nf
\fB> unregister 0x03\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Unregister Disconnection Complete event handler
.nf
\fB> unregister 0x05\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Unregister LE Meta event handler
.nf
\fB> unregister 0x3e\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS close
.sp
Close HCI channel.
.sp
Closes the currently open HCI channel.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> close\fP
.TP
.B Example Close the current HCI channel
.nf
\fB> close\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
